I struggle with in person interactions. I dont like talking to people, I dont like people being in my space. I have mental illnesses & speech impediments that make it incredibly difficult for me to hold genuine conversations with people in person & bc of that it’s hard to connect

As a child, I joined so many different clubs and took lessons and did activities and nothing ever brought me joy. I got bored with everything, I still get bored with everything. My parents struggled with it bc I simply didn’t give a shit about anything, even in elementary school.

I turn 30 in May and I’m having a crisis bc I’ve spent my entire life trying to figure out what it is exactly that I want to do with myself and finding a space where I feel comfortable but at the end of the day, every day, I feel like I simply don’t belong anywhere doing anything
